/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=markh","name":"markh","emailAddress":"markharw00d at yahoo dot co dot uk","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mark Harwood","active":true},"created":"2010-07-13T12:41:52.031+0000","updated":"2010-07-13T12:41:52.031+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12469162/comment/12887757","id":"12887757","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=markh","name":"markh","emailAddress":"markharw00d at yahoo dot co dot uk","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mark Harwood","active":true},"body":"Looks like on the \"close\" call IndexWriter is flushing a superfluous \".del\" file of buffered deletes.\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=markh","name":"markh","emailAddress":"markharw00d at yahoo dot co dot uk","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mark Harwood","active":true},"created":"2010-07-13T13:32:57.775+0000","updated":"2010-07-13T13:32:57.775+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12469162/comment/12887771","id":"12887771","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=shaie","name":"shaie","emailAddress":"serera at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Shai Erera","active":true},"body":"It did not fail for me on 3.1, however did fail on 3.0.1.\r\n\r\nI'm attaching a version of this test, which creates far less docs (5, instead of 10,000) and uses a RAMDirectory). The test still fails, which is expected. I assume if we want to make that an official unit test, the test case which passes should go away? (or not)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=shaie","name":"shaie","emailAddress":"serera at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Shai Erera","active":true},"created":"2010-07-13T14:18:16.696+0000","updated":"2010-07-13T14:18:16.696+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12469162/comment/12887775","id":"12887775","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mikemccand","name":"mikemccand","emailAddress":"lucene at mikemccandless dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael McCandless","active":true},"body":"Duh -- in DocumentsWriter.abort, right after deletesInRAM.clear() we must add deletesFlush.clear().  So, indeed, any deletions pending (either due to .updateDoc or .deleteDocs) when segments were flushed, fail to be cleared and are then applied on close.\r\n\r\nHow awful!","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mikemccand","name":"mikemccand","emailAddress":"lucene at mikemccandless dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael McCandless","active":true},"created":"2010-07-13T14:35:35.656+0000","updated":"2010-07-13T14:35:35.656+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12469162/comment/12887785","id":"12887785","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mikemccand","name":"mikemccand","emailAddress":"lucene at mikemccandless dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael McCandless","active":true},"body":"Attached patch -- started from Shai's patch, tweaked it a bit, added the one line fix & CHANGES entry.\r\n\r\nI see the test in fact failing on 3.x.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?usern